üìò PROJECT GUIDE ‚Äî Grade Calculator Pro (JavaFX GUI Application)
1. ABSTRACT

Grade Calculator Pro is a JavaFX-based desktop application designed to simplify academic grade calculation for students.
The system allows users to enter subjects, marks, and credits, and automatically calculates SGPA, percentage, and individual subject grades.
Featuring a modern graphical user interface (GUI), the software eliminates manual calculations and provides instant, accurate results.
The application is built on an MVC architecture ensuring clean code, scalability, and easy maintainability.

This project demonstrates real-world software development practices utilizing Java, JavaFX, OOP, MVC architecture, and GUI design principles.

2. INTRODUCTION

In academic institutions, calculating student grades manually can be time-consuming and error-prone.
Traditional methods involve manually converting marks into grade points, calculating weighted averages, and ensuring accuracy.
Grade Calculator Pro automates this process, reduces errors, and provides a clean, user-friendly interface for quick results.

The application is ideal for:

Students

Faculty

Academic administrators

It can be extended to a complete student performance management system in the future.

3. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Manual grade calculation is slow and prone to mistakes, especially when dealing with:

Multiple subjects

Varying credit values

Different grading standards

SGPA/CGPA formulas

There is a need for an easy-to-use system which:

Reduces human calculation errors

Saves time

Provides instant results

Is visually appealing and accessible

4. OBJECTIVES

The main objectives of Grade Calculator Pro are:

Provide an automated system for grade and SGPA calculation.

Ensure 100% accuracy in academic calculations.

Present results clearly with a modern GUI.

Follow a structured software architecture (MVC + OOP).

Allow easy addition of multiple subjects dynamically.

Increase usability through an intuitive JavaFX interface.

5. EXISTING SYSTEM

The existing systems include:

